  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7033 sitting just above the massive +12.9B gamma wall at 7030, dealers are actively selling into this strength to hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime with 124B total GEX suggests dealers will continue providing liquidity by selling rallies and buying dips, with the tight 7015-7030 negative/positive gamma band creating a strong gravitational pull for mean reversion. Watch for rejection at the 7050 wall (+12.1B) if we push higher, while any break below 7030 should find support from dealer buying between 7015-7000.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect choppy action with dealers capping upside around 7030-7050.",
